The paper deals with the computation of equilibria in biased games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms used in the paper involve combinatorial and optimization techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and the existence of equilibria, which are topics in computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper uses approximation algorithms, which are often studied in machine learning (cs.LG).
